    description: "Tucson at 2,389 feet elevation is notably cooler than Phoenix, averaging about 10°F lower in summer. The city is surrounded by five mountain ranges that generate dramatic localized thunderstorms during the intense monsoon season. Summer days can be extremely hot but the elevation brings cooler nights.",
    districts: [
