    lat: 46.7867,
    lon: -92.1005,
    timezone: 'America/Chicago',
    description: "Duluth on the western tip of Lake Superior has the most dramatic lake-effect climate in the country. Lake Superior — the world's largest freshwater lake — keeps the city remarkably cool in summer (rarely above 80°F) while lake-effect snowstorms can be intense. The city's dramatic hillside topography creates strong elevation weather differences.",
    districts: [
