    description: "Portland in the Willamette Valley between the Coast Range and Cascades has a classic Pacific Northwest marine climate. The city is famous for its mild, rainy winters and warm, sunny summers. The 2021 Heat Dome brought temperatures to 116°F, shattering records and causing hundreds of deaths — an extreme event showing climate change impacts on a city with minimal air conditioning.",
    districts: [
      { name: 'Downtown Portland', slug: 'portland-or-downtown', lat: 45.5051, lon: -122.6750, description: "Portland's Pioneer Courthouse Square and urban core is compressed by the Willamette River to the east and the West Hills to the west, creating channeled winds and some valley fog." },
      { name: 'Pearl District', slug: 'portland-pearl', lat: 45.5242, lon: -122.6837, description: "The Pearl's dense condo towers have created a heat island in the old warehouse district — the 2021 heat dome was devastating here without AC." },
      { name: 'Northeast Portland', slug: 'portland-ne', lat: 45.5536, lon: -122.6390, description: "NE Portland's extensive residential canopy of mature oaks and maples helped moderate 2021 heat dome impacts compared to less-treed areas." },
