    description: "El Paso at 3,800 feet in the Chihuahuan Desert is one of America's sunniest cities with over 300 days of sunshine. The Franklin Mountains bisect the city and the Rio Grande forms the border with Ciudad Juárez, Mexico. The high desert elevation means summer days are hot but nights cool significantly, making El Paso's summer more bearable than coastal Texas cities.",
